00:14:41.620 --> 00:14:43.592
Now this is widely reported.

00:14:43.592 --> 00:14:45.300
We did know that they
were party animals.

00:14:45.300 --> 00:14:47.050
We're never really
going to know the truth

00:14:47.050 --> 00:14:49.070
because Crick is dead.

00:14:49.070 --> 00:14:52.080
However, we do know that
this jerk, Kary Mullis,

00:14:52.080 --> 00:14:58.390
who got the Nobel Prize in 1992,
achieved his insight from LSD.

00:14:58.390 --> 00:15:00.891
How many people here have
a biology background?

00:15:00.891 --> 00:15:01.890
Mostly you're engineers.

00:15:01.890 --> 00:15:05.240
OK, who here has heard of the
polymerase chain reaction?

00:15:05.240 --> 00:15:06.860
So this got the Nobel Prize.

00:15:06.860 --> 00:15:08.890
I do not have time to
explain how it works.

00:15:08.890 --> 00:15:10.850
But it truly was a
stroke of genius.

00:15:10.850 --> 00:15:13.390
Before he came up with
this in the 1980s,

00:15:13.390 --> 00:15:17.860
it took geneticists years to
unravel the language of DNA.

00:15:17.860 --> 00:15:19.910
With this simple
insight, just take it,

00:15:19.910 --> 00:15:22.320
shatter it into 1,000
shards, read them separately,

00:15:22.320 --> 00:15:23.650
and put them back together.

00:15:23.650 --> 00:15:26.660
He really did earn
the Nobel Prize.

00:15:26.660 --> 00:15:28.645
And he got this insight on LSD.

00:15:28.645 --> 00:15:30.270
And I'm not making
this up because it's

00:15:30.270 --> 00:15:35.420
in his autobiography,
"Dancing in the Mind Field."

00:15:35.420 --> 00:15:38.090
"DNA chains coiled and floated.

00:15:38.090 --> 00:15:41.740
Lurid blue and pink images
of electric molecules

00:15:41.740 --> 00:15:44.800
injected themselves somewhere
between the mountain road

00:15:44.800 --> 00:15:47.100
and my eyes."

00:15:47.100 --> 00:15:51.670
What are the two most
important words in this quote?

00:15:51.670 --> 00:15:54.770
Mountain road-- he was on
acid and he was driving.

00:15:54.770 --> 00:15:57.610
And his wife was asleep
in the seat next to him.

00:15:57.610 --> 00:16:02.514
So here we have Kary Mullis
with-- Ken Kesey with the Merry

00:16:02.514 --> 00:16:04.930
Pranksters, you know, "Electric
Kool-Aid Acid Test," blah,

00:16:04.930 --> 00:16:06.440
blah, blah, taking
acid and speed,

00:16:06.440 --> 00:16:09.023
driving around, taking more acid
and speed and driving around.

00:16:09.023 --> 00:16:12.500
A Nobel Prize-winning geneticist
